docs.abstract: Fears are growing that the worldwide economic downturn could be especially deep and lengthy, with recovery limited by continued anxiety.

docs.abstract: After a strong first two months of the year, sales tumbled in March as Americans stayed home.
docs.snippet: After a strong first two months of the year, sales tumbled in March as Americans stayed home.
docs.lead_paragraph: Automakers reported a plunge on Wednesday in new-vehicle sales as fear of the coronavirus and stay-at-home orders kept consumers from dealerships, adding to the troubles of the country’s largest manufacturing sector.

headline.main: Auto Sales Plummet in First Quarter as Coronavirus Keeps Buyers Away
headline.print_headline: With Buyers Sitting Tight, Carmakers Post Dismal Sales Numbers

docs.abstract: Just before the start of HBO Max, AT&T names Jason Kilar as the head of its entertainment and news unit. He replaces John Stankey, who remains AT&T’s president.
docs.snippet: Just before the start of HBO Max, AT&T names Jason Kilar as the head of its entertainment and news unit. He replaces John Stankey, who remains AT&T’s president.
docs.lead_paragraph: AT&T announced on Wednesday that it would bring in the former head of Hulu to lead WarnerMedia, the news and entertainment division that includes HBO, CNN and the Warner Bros. movie studio.

headline.main: Former Hulu Boss Will Lead WarnerMedia, Home of HBO and CNN
headline.print_headline: Ex-Hulu Boss Will Oversee WarnerMedia Properties

docs.abstract: The activist hedge fund Elliott Management has taken a sizable stake in Twitter and called for changes at the social network.
docs.snippet: The activist hedge fund Elliott Management has taken a sizable stake in Twitter and called for changes at the social network.
docs.lead_paragraph: One of Wall Street’s most powerful activist hedge funds has taken a stake in Twitter and intends to shake up the social network — including by potentially calling for the replacement of its founder, Jack Dorsey, as chief executive, two people briefed on the matter said on Saturday.

headline.main: Hedge Fund May Push for Ouster of Jack Dorsey as Twitter’s C.E.O.
headline.print_headline: Hedge Fund Wants to Shake Up Twitter, Starting at the Top

byline.original: By Michael J. de la Merced and Kate Conger

docs.abstract: Robert Swan, who leads the world’s biggest chip maker, is pushing his 110,000 employees to confront internal problems more openly.
docs.snippet: Robert Swan, who leads the world’s biggest chip maker, is pushing his 110,000 employees to confront internal problems more openly.
docs.lead_paragraph: SANTA CLARA, Calif. — Since last spring, workers at Intel who turned on their corporate laptops or wall displays inside the company’s more than 1,000 conference rooms have seen a new tagline: “One Intel.”

headline.main: Intel’s Culture Needed Fixing. Its C.E.O. Is Shaking Things Up.
headline.print_headline: Chip Maker Is Retooling Its Culture

docs.abstract: Alphabet’s self-driving unit, a pioneer in autonomous vehicle research, has been expanding its commercial efforts.
docs.snippet: Alphabet’s self-driving unit, a pioneer in autonomous vehicle research, has been expanding its commercial efforts.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — More than a decade after Google started experimenting with driverless cars, Waymo, the autonomous vehicle unit of Google’s parent company, Alphabet, says it has raised $2.25 billion, mostly from outside investors.

headline.main: Waymo Includes Outsiders in $2.25 Billion Investment Round

docs.abstract: A settlement for as much as $500 million would resolve a lawsuit accusing Apple of slowing old iPhones as it released new ones.
docs.snippet: A settlement for as much as $500 million would resolve a lawsuit accusing Apple of slowing old iPhones as it released new ones.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Many iPhone owners believe Apple purposely slowed down their old devices as it released new ones. Now some of them might be in line for a small payday: Apple has agreed to pay some iPhone owners about $25 each to settle such complaints.

headline.main: Apple Agrees to Pay Some iPhone Owners $25 Each
headline.print_headline: Apple Settles a Claim  It Slowed Down Phones

docs.abstract: The 14 states holding primaries can be sorted into four general types: aging, rising, brainy or booming. (Minnesota and Virginia may be more alike than you think.)
docs.snippet: The 14 states holding primaries can be sorted into four general types: aging, rising, brainy or booming. (Minnesota and Virginia may be more alike than you think.)
docs.lead_paragraph: The first few contests in the Democratic presidential primary race have been fought in states that are small and somewhat quirky economically. There aren’t many states where voters care as much about ethanol subsidies as they do in Iowa, or where culinary unions wield as much power as in Nevada.

headline.main: Super Tuesday State Economies Will Test Democrats
headline.print_headline: Super Tuesday May Also Serve as an Economic Gauge

docs.abstract: The central bank will streamline how bank capital requirements are set, despite objections by a Fed governor who said the move would lower the amount of cash banks keep on hand.
docs.snippet: The central bank will streamline how bank capital requirements are set, despite objections by a Fed governor who said the move would lower the amount of cash banks keep on hand.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Federal Reserve on Wednesday moved to simplify capital rules, a long-expected change that banks have been pushing for — and one that sharply divided central bank officials.

headline.main: The Fed Simplifies Capital Rules, a Change Sought by Big Banks
headline.print_headline: Fed Eases Bank Rules, Despite Dissent From Lone Obama Governor
